# MLOps Infrastructure & Open Model Deployment | 2026-04-03

## 🔥 Story of the Day
### Docker Hub becomes central repository for packaging AI models as OCI artifacts [Gemma 4 is Here: Now Available on Docker Hub](https://www.docker.com/blog/gemma4-dockerhub/) — Docker Blog
Docker Hub is evolving into a primary distribution point for packaged AI models, treating them as standard OCI artifacts. The latest open model, Gemma 4, is now available in this container-ready format. This shift standardizes model packaging, making it significantly easier for engineers to integrate ML components into established container ecosystems.

For those managing ML infrastructure on Kubernetes, this removes reliance on custom model-specific tooling. By adopting the OCI standard, developers can pipeline model deployments using existing CI/CD tooling, security scanning, and automation patterns without needing bespoke integrations for every new model release.

A key technical detail to note is the simple consumption command: `docker model pull gemma4`. This level of standardization drastically lowers the operational burden of moving models from research/training environments into production, making portability from edge devices to large clusters seamless.

